Union Bank has announced its partnership with TEDxLagos for the upcom-ing TEDxLagos event scheduled for August 18. This is part of the bank’s efforts to leverage partnerships and initiatives that support and promote Nigeria’s development and growth. TEDx is a global platform created in the spirit of TED’s mission, “ideas worth sharing”. The Lagos event will focus on bringing together some of Nigeria’s best minds; entrepreneurs and social entrepreneurs, professionals, innovators and reformers to share thought provoking ideas that will encourage decisive action for the benefit of the society. Speaking on the bank’s partnership with TEDxLagos, Head, Corporate Communications and Marketing at Union Bank, Ogochukwu Ekezie-Ekaidem said: “Union Bank is excited about this partnership with TEDxLagos; a platform synonymous with sharing and inspiring great ideas.”  